<h1>Problem 916 - 2019 IMOSL, A5</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 9</h2>
<p>Let \(x_1, x_2, \dots, x_n\) be different real numbers. Prove that \[\sum_{1 \leqslant i \leqslant n} \prod_{j \neq i} \frac{1-x_{i}x_{j}}{x_{i}-x_{j}}=\left\{\begin{array}{ll} 0, & \text { if } n \text { is even; } \\ 1, & \text { if } n \text { is odd. } \end{array}\right.\]</p>
